<div class="callout">
  <div class="callout-title">Anchor question</div>
  Is Earth special, or is it one of many habitable planets we just haven't found yet?
</div>

<div class="prose">
  <p>Unit 1 launches <strong>Thread 2 — Systems Thinking</strong> formally, with the first student-built systems diagram of Earth's subsystems. It also extends <strong>Thread 1 — OPVL</strong> from Unit 0 to planetary data sources: NASA exoplanet archive entries, peer-reviewed astronomy summaries, AI explanations of habitability.</p>
  <p>The unit anchors on three cases: <strong>Earth</strong> (the baseline), <strong>Mars</strong> (the failed-habitable case that shows how easily habitability can be lost), and <strong>one exoplanet of the student's choosing</strong> (the unknown). The summative — the <a href="/units/unit-1/assessment-goldilocks-report/">Goldilocks Report</a> — is the structured comparative analysis. The Stakeholder Q&A in Block 10 introduces the audience-defense format students will use in every subsequent unit summative.</p>
  <p>Scale is genuinely beyond intuition for most learners. Every cosmic claim in this unit is anchored to a comparison students can grasp — Chennai-to-Mumbai, an A4 page, a school year.</p>
</div>

<section aria-label="Unit 1 blocks" style="margin-top: 24px;">
  <h2 style="font-size: 22px; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 12px;">The ten blocks</h2>
  <div class="section-grid">
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-1/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 1 — Phenomenon Launch</div>
      <div class="card-desc">What makes a planet habitable? Side-by-side images of Earth, Mars, Venus, and TRAPPIST-1e. Students list factors before the unit teaches them anything.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-2/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 2 — Earth as Baseline</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Systems thinking launches. Students name Earth's four subsystems and draw a first systems diagram with at least one interaction.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-3/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 3 — Mars as Calibration</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Compare Earth and Mars. What Mars had, what it lost, why. Apply the early habitability framework to Mars and identify where it fails.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-4/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 4 — Scale of the Cosmos</div>
      <div class="card-desc">AU, light-year, habitable zone. Students place 5+ objects at correct relative scale. Goldilocks Report assigned today.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-5/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 5 — Exoplanet Detection</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Transit method. What a light curve tells us (size, period) and what it doesn't (composition, life). Read a real transit dip.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-6/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 6 — Choose Your Exoplanet</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Work through the 8 exoplanet data cards. Pick one for the Goldilocks Report. Identify two questions you'll need to answer.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-7/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 7 — Habitability Framework</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Complete the Habitability Framework Template for all three planets. Color-code each criterion MEETS / PARTIAL / FAILS with reasoning.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-8/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 8 — Drafting Day</div>
      <div class="card-desc">First full draft of the Goldilocks Report. ≥4 sources cited (incl. NASA Exoplanet Archive). AI Documentation section completed.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-9/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 9 — Stakeholder Q&A Prep</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Rehearse against the Q&A bank in pairs. Identify the strongest objection to your verdict and prepare your response.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/block-10/">
      <div class="card-title">Block 10 — NASA Committee Defense</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Defend the Goldilocks Report to peers playing the NASA evaluation committee. Unit reflection.</div>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

